1
00:01:31,691 --> 00:01:35,354
Ma! Señora Nunez came in.
She's burning up with fever.

2
00:01:35,528 --> 00:01:38,497
Go cool her head.
Recite the 23rd Psalm.

3
00:01:38,665 --> 00:01:40,189
l'll be there in a bit.

4
00:01:52,278 --> 00:01:56,044
New Mexico, 1 885

5
00:01:57,217 --> 00:02:00,618
''Though l walk through the valley of
the shadow of death, l fear no evil.''

6
00:02:00,787 --> 00:02:03,688
-Morning, kids.
-''Thou art with me. Thy rod and staff...

7
00:02:04,257 --> 00:02:06,555
...they comfort me.

8
00:02:06,726 --> 00:02:10,355
Thou preparest a table before me
in the presence of mine enemies.

9
00:02:10,530 --> 00:02:13,795
Thou anointest my head with oil.
My cup runneth over.

10
00:02:15,101 --> 00:02:19,697
Surely goodness and mercy shall
follow me all the days of my life.''

11
00:02:19,873 --> 00:02:23,832
Darling, get me some Cocea paste
and my tooth plier, please.

12
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:25,944
Yes, ma'am.

13
00:02:30,783 --> 00:02:32,011
No. No.

14
00:02:36,156 --> 00:02:39,057
She don't worry about the pain. No.

15
00:02:39,225 --> 00:02:42,820
lt is her only tooth.
She worry how she look.

16
00:02:42,996 --> 00:02:44,827
Thank you.

17
00:02:51,371 --> 00:02:53,100
Thank you.

18
00:03:00,113 --> 00:03:02,547
l need you to hold
your grandmother down.

19
00:03:02,715 --> 00:03:05,240
Darling, can you hold her arm?

20
00:03:06,452 --> 00:03:09,546
Pin that, Dot. Hold her nose.
Hold her nose.

21
00:03:14,627 --> 00:03:16,254
Careful.

22
00:03:36,616 --> 00:03:38,914
l hate to ask...

23
00:03:39,519 --> 00:03:41,919
...but can you pay me for this today?

24
00:03:58,338 --> 00:04:01,739
Jumping <i>pinches</i> coyotes
sons of bitches.

25
00:04:01,908 --> 00:04:04,877
That lightning sure did kill her.

26
00:04:11,184 --> 00:04:14,950
This calf won't last the night out here.
Let's put her in the barn.

27
00:04:18,258 --> 00:04:19,691
Señor Brake.

28
00:04:26,733 --> 00:04:28,098
lndian.

29
00:04:28,501 --> 00:04:29,991
Apache, maybe.

30
00:04:30,603 --> 00:04:34,539
Some kind of Apache
son of a bitch.

31
00:04:55,094 --> 00:04:57,153
Good day, sir.

32
00:05:00,800 --> 00:05:03,166
l said, hello.

33
00:05:05,438 --> 00:05:08,464
That your man over there
in the trees?

34
00:05:13,479 --> 00:05:18,075
What is he planning on doing
with that carbine?

35
00:05:18,251 --> 00:05:20,549
We've had trouble
with coyotes killing calves.

36
00:05:20,720 --> 00:05:23,621
Tell him l'm not a coyote.

37
00:05:31,497 --> 00:05:32,896
ls that the healer's place?

38
00:05:33,966 --> 00:05:35,399
You come for doctoring?

39
00:06:02,395 --> 00:06:04,454
Lady shuts her doors at sundown.

40
00:06:05,865 --> 00:06:08,095
She's pretty firm about her hours.

41
00:06:08,267 --> 00:06:11,202
You're welcome to spend the night,
see her in the morning.

42
00:06:11,537 --> 00:06:13,300
l thank you kindly.

43
00:06:19,512 --> 00:06:21,571
Barn's this way, mister.

44
00:06:45,071 --> 00:06:47,505
There's a spare bunk
over there, Mr....

45
00:06:48,374 --> 00:06:50,569
Mr. Fernandez.

46
00:06:51,744 --> 00:06:55,145
Jones. The man that owned
that saddle tried to kill me.

47
00:06:55,348 --> 00:06:59,114
l was living with the Jicarilla. l
suppose he thought l was one of them.

48
00:06:59,719 --> 00:07:01,380
You're Apache, huh?

49
00:07:02,488 --> 00:07:05,013
-What did you say?
-Forget it.

50
00:07:05,691 --> 00:07:07,249
What did you say?

51
00:07:15,701 --> 00:07:17,293
Come over here.

52
00:07:19,972 --> 00:07:21,371
Now, l mean it!

53
00:07:22,809 --> 00:07:25,243
There'll be no trouble here.

54
00:07:25,411 --> 00:07:28,608
lf that's too tough for you to
understand, you can move on.

55
00:07:45,598 --> 00:07:47,065
Emiliano, unpack his mule.

56
00:07:47,233 --> 00:07:50,691
You will keep your hands
off of my mule...

57
00:07:51,404 --> 00:07:54,305
...Emiliano.

58
00:08:13,626 --> 00:08:16,117
-Don't slam that door.
-Yes, ma'am.

59
00:08:16,295 --> 00:08:19,560
There are houses in Cleveland
with lamps that run on electricity.

60
00:08:19,732 --> 00:08:21,927
l'd like to see Cleveland.

61
00:08:30,543 --> 00:08:33,137
-Can you fetch the water, please, Dot?
-Yes, ma'am.

62
00:08:36,916 --> 00:08:41,285
At the fair, there's gonna be
expositions of the future.

63
00:08:41,454 --> 00:08:45,049
There's gonna be a graphophone. You
can hear your own voice back on it.

64
00:08:45,925 --> 00:08:48,655
-The Dickersons are going.
-Brake can't spare you.

65
00:08:50,162 --> 00:08:52,790
-Ma.
-Not tomorrow with the cows calving.

66
00:08:52,965 --> 00:08:56,560
-The Fosters too.
-Got all the future you need right here.

67
00:08:57,169 --> 00:09:00,332
Riding all day with this
cramping and all.

68
00:09:09,582 --> 00:09:12,915
Don't you ever act helpless
and pitiable to win favor with a man.

69
00:09:13,085 --> 00:09:16,350
Some people shouldn't give advice
on how to act with men.

70
00:09:17,390 --> 00:09:21,690
-And it's ''pitiful'' in English.
-You heard what l said.

71
00:09:22,762 --> 00:09:24,127
That pail's half-empty.

72
00:09:24,297 --> 00:09:28,063
l didn't do it. lt's that old lndian's
dumb old mule.

73
00:09:28,234 --> 00:09:31,567
-What lndian?
-Some drifter looking for doctoring.

74
00:09:33,306 --> 00:09:35,001
lf you're gonna eat barefoot...

75
00:09:35,174 --> 00:09:37,768
...why not take supper
with the animals in the barn.

76
00:09:37,944 --> 00:09:41,710
My boots don't fit no more.
Cut off my blood circulation.

77
00:09:41,881 --> 00:09:45,282
-lt's your birthday soon.
-l'll have gangrene by then.

78
00:09:45,451 --> 00:09:50,252
Your mother may have to saw off your
feet, then. Like poor old Mr. Swenson.

79
00:09:56,862 --> 00:09:58,659
Mr. Jones.

80
00:10:00,132 --> 00:10:03,124
Maggie, this is the visiting gentleman
l mentioned.

81
00:10:05,137 --> 00:10:08,129
l'll bet a warm meal
sounds pretty good to you.

82
00:10:09,342 --> 00:10:11,276
Magdalena.

83
00:10:24,790 --> 00:10:28,248
l'm afraid we have
just enough food for family.

84
00:10:28,794 --> 00:10:31,820
We can't be offering
our hospitality tonight.

85
00:10:33,499 --> 00:10:36,332
-l'm sure we can all do with less.
-l'm sure we can't!

86
00:10:38,137 --> 00:10:41,072
l have two growing girls to feed.

87
00:10:41,474 --> 00:10:43,169
Maggie?

88
00:10:47,680 --> 00:10:49,477
Maggie.

89
00:10:55,688 --> 00:10:58,782
Lilly, why don't you say grace.

90
00:11:12,338 --> 00:11:14,329
Who is he?

91
00:11:17,009 --> 00:11:19,341
Called you Magdalena.

92
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:22,940
Your hair bristles
when you lay eyes on him.

93
00:11:23,115 --> 00:11:24,946
He scares me, is all.

94
00:11:25,918 --> 00:11:29,183
-Nobody scares you.
-Can't trust him.

95
00:11:29,355 --> 00:11:31,949
Maggie, who is he?

96
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:43,132
He's my father.

97
00:11:48,240 --> 00:11:51,334
-l thought your father was dead.
-He is.

98
00:11:51,510 --> 00:11:53,569
To me, he is.

99
00:11:55,147 --> 00:11:56,876
l want him gone, Brake.

100
00:11:57,416 --> 00:11:59,475
Gone? He's your kin.
You just can't--

101
00:11:59,652 --> 00:12:03,452
He ran off when l wasn't Dot's age.
Went lndian.

102
00:12:03,622 --> 00:12:06,318
Turn your back,
he'll eat your horses and dogs.

103
00:12:06,826 --> 00:12:09,488
He's being chased...

104
00:12:09,662 --> 00:12:12,722
...or running from something,
l don't know what.

105
00:12:12,898 --> 00:12:15,924
But he's bad, Brake. l swear.

106
00:12:16,102 --> 00:12:19,503
l do not want him
near my children.

107
00:12:22,608 --> 00:12:26,840
We're lndians, Lilly.
We're lndians.

108
00:12:37,423 --> 00:12:39,721
Does he do that all night?

109
00:12:40,292 --> 00:12:42,021
Oh, he's just getting started.

110
00:12:42,194 --> 00:12:45,493
-You come here for the healing?
-ln a manner of speaking.

111
00:12:46,098 --> 00:12:48,396
Thought you might be hungry.

112
00:12:48,567 --> 00:12:50,797
-lt's rabbit stew.
-l can't eat rabbits.

113
00:12:51,137 --> 00:12:54,106
l was bitten by a rattlesnake.

114
00:12:54,940 --> 00:12:56,168
All right.

115
00:12:56,342 --> 00:13:00,039
When there's company,
you sleep in there. ls that right?

116
00:13:00,312 --> 00:13:01,973
That's right.

117
00:13:02,281 --> 00:13:04,977
-You're not her husband?
-No, sir.

118
00:13:07,086 --> 00:13:08,883
Not for lack of asking.

119
00:13:09,255 --> 00:13:10,984
They your children?

120
00:13:11,157 --> 00:13:12,818
No.

121
00:13:12,992 --> 00:13:15,586
What happened to their father?

122
00:13:17,062 --> 00:13:19,257
You don't know this?

123
00:13:23,035 --> 00:13:26,300
l can't say what all happened
between you two...

124
00:13:26,972 --> 00:13:28,564
...but you ain't welcome here.

125
00:13:31,911 --> 00:13:33,845
But she's a good Christian.

126
00:13:35,414 --> 00:13:37,541
She won't turn away any man
in need.

127
00:13:38,217 --> 00:13:41,277
Tomorrow, she'll give you
what doctoring she can...

128
00:13:41,453 --> 00:13:43,546
...then you're on your way.

129
00:13:50,830 --> 00:13:53,162
There's places where a father
would kill a man...

130
00:13:53,332 --> 00:13:56,824
...for doing what you're doing,
you know that, don't you?

131
00:15:34,199 --> 00:15:37,293
lf you have something to say, say it.

132
00:15:37,670 --> 00:15:40,298
Are you really a lndian?

133
00:15:40,639 --> 00:15:43,335
Brake said you rode
with the Chiricahua.

134
00:15:43,509 --> 00:15:45,409
That's right.

135
00:15:45,577 --> 00:15:50,241
-So that means l'm part lndian, right?
-No.

136
00:15:50,916 --> 00:15:53,146
Not at all.

137
00:16:13,138 --> 00:16:17,097
You look stupid trying to work
in those fancy clothes, you know.

138
00:16:17,276 --> 00:16:19,972
l am leaving here as soon as l can.

139
00:16:20,145 --> 00:16:23,046
-l'm moving to the city.
-But Grandpa's visiting.

140
00:16:23,215 --> 00:16:25,080
Did you see him?

141
00:16:25,250 --> 00:16:26,911
He's a savage.

142
00:16:27,086 --> 00:16:29,611
They're gut-eaters, you know.

143
00:16:33,325 --> 00:16:37,523
l was born into the wrong family,
l swear to God l was.

144
00:16:53,479 --> 00:16:55,504
-l appreciate this.
-Take off your shirt.

145
00:16:55,681 --> 00:16:59,913
-Magdalena--
-Don't call me that. lt's not my name.

146
00:17:10,029 --> 00:17:12,395
-Where's it hurt?
-Hurts when l breathe.

147
00:17:12,564 --> 00:17:14,191
Mostly around here.

148
00:17:25,444 --> 00:17:29,710
Yeah. Your muscles are torn
just under your ribs.

149
00:17:29,882 --> 00:17:33,045
You need to put
a cottonwood plaster to it.

150
00:17:36,255 --> 00:17:37,950
You'll live.

151
00:17:38,290 --> 00:17:41,259
l never thought you'd turn out
to be a healer.

152
00:17:42,161 --> 00:17:44,561
l remember you had
that yellow cat one time.

153
00:17:44,730 --> 00:17:47,096
You cried because a badger
bit its tail off.

154
00:17:47,266 --> 00:17:50,997
-Your mother came running--
-Don't remember. Not in front of me.

155
00:17:51,870 --> 00:17:54,236
Because l remember my mother.

156
00:17:54,673 --> 00:17:58,769
My mother died
scrubbing a man's floor.

157
00:17:58,944 --> 00:18:00,275
And you killed her.

158
00:18:00,846 --> 00:18:03,644
Didn't shoot her or stab her,
but what you did....

159
00:18:05,984 --> 00:18:07,315
You broke her!

160
00:18:08,654 --> 00:18:11,589
And l remember my brother too.

161
00:18:11,757 --> 00:18:14,157
He lasted six years.

162
00:18:14,326 --> 00:18:16,590
l bet you never even knew his name.

163
00:18:16,762 --> 00:18:20,596
And l remember praying hard
every night that you'd come home.

164
00:18:20,799 --> 00:18:22,630
On the day l put him
in the ground...

165
00:18:22,801 --> 00:18:25,235
...l remember praying even harder
you were dead.

166
00:18:25,404 --> 00:18:30,569
So you don't want to reminisce
with me, that l promise you.

167
00:18:31,009 --> 00:18:34,103
l earned this money in large part...

168
00:18:34,279 --> 00:18:39,774
...killing mountain lions for ranchers
like you. l want you to have it.

169
00:18:39,952 --> 00:18:42,546
lf l were destitute
and drawing my last breath--

170
00:18:42,721 --> 00:18:45,121
This is good money.
Take it for your children.

171
00:18:45,290 --> 00:18:47,155
-Take it for your funeral.
-Magdalena.

172
00:18:48,560 --> 00:18:51,961
l've done my duty as a Christian.
You get the hell off my ranch!

173
00:18:58,704 --> 00:18:59,966
l'd stop now.

174
00:19:06,311 --> 00:19:07,938
Maggie asked you to leave.

175
00:19:10,549 --> 00:19:13,382
l think it's time you did so, sir.

176
00:19:17,656 --> 00:19:19,283
Right about now.

177
00:19:45,217 --> 00:19:46,878
So long.

178
00:19:51,490 --> 00:19:53,720
Nice making your acquaintance.

179
00:20:07,139 --> 00:20:10,233
What's done is done, l guess.

180
00:20:18,517 --> 00:20:21,543
l know you would have
done different.

181
00:20:24,356 --> 00:20:27,883
l appreciate your regard, Brake.

182
00:20:28,060 --> 00:20:29,652
l do.

183
00:20:50,482 --> 00:20:52,416
Well, night, then.

184
00:20:56,622 --> 00:20:59,455
Did they see you come in?

185
00:21:10,369 --> 00:21:12,599
We can't make a sound.

186
00:21:31,857 --> 00:21:34,257
Figure we can get them
all branded in a day?

187
00:21:34,426 --> 00:21:37,589
-You want Dot to stay for company?
-Brake, you said l could go.

188
00:21:37,763 --> 00:21:40,596
You promised.
Mama, you promised too.

189
00:21:40,766 --> 00:21:44,395
Oh, l'm fine.
He won't be coming back.

190
00:21:45,270 --> 00:21:47,704
This will help the cramping.

191
00:21:50,876 --> 00:21:52,503
The calves are more important...

192
00:21:52,678 --> 00:21:55,112
...than hearing your voice
come out of a machine.

193
00:21:55,280 --> 00:21:59,080
Well, l guess you never had anything
but this. So why should l?

194
00:22:04,256 --> 00:22:05,848
Come on, let's get going.

195
00:22:08,260 --> 00:22:10,888
You sure look frilly
to be working cattle.

196
00:22:12,464 --> 00:22:14,455
l'll keep an eye on them.

197
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:18,091
-Just be home before dark.
-All right.

198
00:22:18,270 --> 00:22:19,999
All right.

199
00:22:45,230 --> 00:22:47,494
Easy now.

200
00:22:47,666 --> 00:22:49,691
That's right.

201
00:24:33,472 --> 00:24:35,497
Dot?

202
00:24:38,343 --> 00:24:40,243
Dot?

203
00:24:41,913 --> 00:24:43,744
Darling?

204
00:24:47,252 --> 00:24:49,584
Get! Get!

205
00:24:54,826 --> 00:24:56,817
Dot?

206
00:27:42,360 --> 00:27:44,419
No!

207
00:27:44,596 --> 00:27:46,826
No!

208
00:28:02,847 --> 00:28:04,508
Dot!

209
00:28:10,388 --> 00:28:12,618
Oh, Lord. Darling.

210
00:28:13,558 --> 00:28:15,321
Mama, l'm cold.

211
00:28:15,493 --> 00:28:20,590
-l'm here, darling. Are you all right?
-l'm cold. l'm cold.

212
00:28:21,332 --> 00:28:25,234
-Mama, l'm cold.
-Darling, where's Lilly?

213
00:28:26,905 --> 00:28:30,432
-Emiliano.
-Yeah, l know.

214
00:28:30,608 --> 00:28:32,633
Darling, where's Lilly?

215
00:28:32,811 --> 00:28:34,540
Emiliano and me...

216
00:28:36,681 --> 00:28:39,343
...we was in the arroyo.

217
00:28:39,551 --> 00:28:44,352
We heard shots from where Brake
and Lilly was.

218
00:28:45,457 --> 00:28:47,721
He told me, ''Stay down''...

219
00:28:47,892 --> 00:28:49,883
...Emiliano did.

220
00:28:50,061 --> 00:28:53,861
''Don't move. Stay down.''

221
00:28:54,032 --> 00:28:56,523
He went to see...

222
00:28:56,868 --> 00:28:59,769
...but he didn't come back.

223
00:28:59,938 --> 00:29:03,704
l waited like he said,
but he didn't come back.

224
00:29:06,377 --> 00:29:09,039
Brake was screaming, Mama.

225
00:29:09,214 --> 00:29:12,615
He screamed so long
l wanted him to stop.

226
00:29:12,784 --> 00:29:14,615
l know. l know it.

227
00:29:14,786 --> 00:29:17,812
-l know it.
-Then he did.

228
00:29:17,989 --> 00:29:21,117
Then someone rode away with Lilly.

229
00:29:23,995 --> 00:29:27,123
l wanted him to stop!

230
00:29:28,133 --> 00:29:29,794
l know it. l know it.

231
00:29:30,702 --> 00:29:33,603
Darling, did you see who?

232
00:29:33,772 --> 00:29:35,296
Who took your sister?

233
00:29:36,941 --> 00:29:38,966
He wore a hood.

234
00:29:39,144 --> 00:29:40,975
He was lndian.

235
00:30:24,155 --> 00:30:28,455
l'm sorry for your loss, ma'am, but l'm
afraid you got the wrong fella in mind.

236
00:30:28,626 --> 00:30:31,652
l've had the man you're describing
in jail since last night.

237
00:30:31,830 --> 00:30:34,993
Sold himself a lion's hide
and got quite a drunk on.

238
00:30:35,166 --> 00:30:37,498
Unacceptable drunk.

239
00:30:37,669 --> 00:30:40,661
He did say he was staying out
by your place, though.

240
00:30:40,839 --> 00:30:43,569
There's been raids like this
on people here lately...

241
00:30:43,741 --> 00:30:45,641
...in Arizona and New Mexico.

242
00:30:45,810 --> 00:30:50,179
Some Apaches jumped the reservation
at San Carlos middle of last month.

243
00:30:50,348 --> 00:30:54,079
We've been getting communications
about them near every day.

244
00:30:55,520 --> 00:30:57,818
To Fort Bowie.

245
00:30:57,989 --> 00:30:59,752
From me.

246
00:31:01,259 --> 00:31:06,094
Possible your hostiles
attacked local ranch.

247
00:31:06,264 --> 00:31:10,064
Two dead, one girl missing.

248
00:31:10,235 --> 00:31:11,862
Named....

249
00:31:12,437 --> 00:31:13,904
Lilly Gilkeson.

250
00:31:14,939 --> 00:31:17,169
Lilly Gilkeson.

251
00:31:17,342 --> 00:31:19,333
