00:57:51,234 --> 00:57:52,792
Get up!

503
00:57:53,870 --> 00:57:55,838
Trying to make a fool of me.

504
00:58:01,344 --> 00:58:03,369
lt's gonna be all right.

505
00:58:19,262 --> 00:58:22,663
l think my feet grew two sizes today.

506
00:58:25,168 --> 00:58:26,863
Try these.

507
00:58:34,644 --> 00:58:37,909
-They're beautiful.
-They were my wife's.

508
00:58:39,849 --> 00:58:41,077
My grandmother?

509
00:58:45,922 --> 00:58:47,514
No.

510
00:59:35,572 --> 00:59:37,130
Mama!

511
00:59:38,708 --> 00:59:40,107
-Mama!
-Dot?

512
00:59:42,712 --> 00:59:44,543
You all right?

513
00:59:44,714 --> 00:59:47,114
You get bit?
Did those snakes bite you?

514
00:59:47,283 --> 00:59:48,648
No.

515
00:59:49,118 --> 00:59:50,983
Mama, a dead man's in there.

516
00:59:52,188 --> 00:59:54,520
Don't worry about that child.

517
00:59:56,426 --> 00:59:58,087
Go on now.

518
01:00:02,265 --> 01:00:03,630
Mama, look at his eyes.

519
01:00:08,972 --> 01:00:11,873
-What happened to him?
-He lost control of his wagon.

520
01:00:12,375 --> 01:00:13,842
Maybe he had a heart seizure.

521
01:00:14,010 --> 01:00:17,138
He didn't have a heart seizure.
His heart's in that hole.

522
01:00:41,971 --> 01:00:43,529
What's behind her head?

523
01:00:46,509 --> 01:00:49,842
-Some people would think it's a sign.
-A good sign or bad sign?

524
01:00:50,013 --> 01:00:52,379
lt wasn't a very good sign for him.
Come here.

525
01:00:55,618 --> 01:00:58,246
-What are you doing?
-These are for protection.

526
01:00:58,421 --> 01:01:01,083
The man who did this is a <i>brujo</i>.

527
01:01:01,257 --> 01:01:03,691
-A what?
-lt's a witch.

528
01:01:03,860 --> 01:01:05,259
You need to wear one too.

529
01:01:05,428 --> 01:01:08,761
You can believe in your witchcraft
and your impiety all you want.

530
01:01:09,232 --> 01:01:11,325
l believe in what l've seen, girl.

531
01:01:11,501 --> 01:01:14,698
Snakes belong on the ground.
This one hangs them in the air.

532
01:01:14,871 --> 01:01:18,864
A man's heart holds his spirit. This
one digs it out and throws it in the dirt.

533
01:01:19,042 --> 01:01:20,270
Don't you start this.

534
01:01:20,443 --> 01:01:23,435
l know a <i>brujo</i> who'd put an arrow
in you a mile away.

535
01:01:23,613 --> 01:01:27,174
l know a <i>brujo</i> who laid his hand
on a child one time. One time.

536
01:01:27,350 --> 01:01:30,547
The child cramped up, fell down
and spit up bees till she died.

537
01:01:30,720 --> 01:01:34,451
-You stop this. You're scaring her.
-She needs to be scared. So do you.

538
01:01:34,624 --> 01:01:37,684
Mama, please. Please.

539
01:01:45,935 --> 01:01:47,698
Just on her.

540
01:02:25,074 --> 01:02:28,134
We gotta get through that canyon
before the storm hits.

541
01:02:28,311 --> 01:02:30,074
You go on and l'll follow.

542
01:02:37,587 --> 01:02:40,579
Give me some of the medical stuff
they stole, the laudanum.

543
01:02:40,757 --> 01:02:42,691
You like that stuff.

544
01:02:45,228 --> 01:02:48,254
You know, l drink enough
of this stuff, l swear...

545
01:02:48,431 --> 01:02:51,229
-...you start to look good to me.
-Hey.

546
01:02:52,502 --> 01:02:55,437
They give this to my grandma
when she was fixing to croak.

547
01:03:32,842 --> 01:03:34,070
Mama!

548
01:03:35,178 --> 01:03:37,237
Mama!

549
01:03:38,414 --> 01:03:40,075
l'll get her!

550
01:03:40,983 --> 01:03:43,076
Get those horses to higher ground!

551
01:03:43,352 --> 01:03:44,910
l've got her!

552
01:03:59,936 --> 01:04:01,597
Dot, you hold on to me!

553
01:04:28,297 --> 01:04:30,197
My foot's caught!

554
01:04:46,282 --> 01:04:48,944
Hold your breath! Right now!

555
01:05:43,272 --> 01:05:44,500
Gotta piss.

556
01:06:13,903 --> 01:06:15,461
Sit up.

557
01:06:19,675 --> 01:06:21,643
l can get us out of here.

558
01:06:22,979 --> 01:06:25,573
-Do you hear that?
-You mustn't speak.

559
01:06:25,748 --> 01:06:27,978
My baby's calling me.

560
01:06:28,517 --> 01:06:31,077
No. l'm sorry. l'm so sorry.

561
01:06:31,587 --> 01:06:34,021
Your baby's passed on.

562
01:06:34,924 --> 01:06:37,984
No. That's just how she sleeps.

563
01:06:38,694 --> 01:06:41,561
There's nothing you can do,
so please just--

564
01:06:48,704 --> 01:06:51,605
There, there. My baby.

565
01:07:02,585 --> 01:07:06,112
Here. Watch out while l get
the horses.

566
01:07:11,327 --> 01:07:14,558
Hey. Just going to get
those berries l promised you.

567
01:07:14,730 --> 01:07:16,357
Don't wander off.

568
01:07:25,307 --> 01:07:27,366
Lord, forgive me.

569
01:07:49,865 --> 01:07:51,230
Stop squirming.

570
01:07:53,569 --> 01:07:56,470
-Goddamn you!
-Give her to me.

571
01:07:56,639 --> 01:07:58,106
-Get up!
-No!

572
01:07:58,274 --> 01:08:00,265
-l got her.
-No!

573
01:08:00,443 --> 01:08:02,809
-Tie her legs!
-Shut up!

574
01:08:03,345 --> 01:08:04,505
Shut up!

575
01:08:04,680 --> 01:08:06,807
Why?

576
01:08:08,217 --> 01:08:11,812
Now we're gonna be back to seven,
and seven's an unlucky number.

577
01:08:13,222 --> 01:08:15,520
Whore! Stop!

578
01:08:31,807 --> 01:08:33,240
Thank you.

579
01:08:35,311 --> 01:08:36,869
Crawl.

580
01:08:37,580 --> 01:08:40,606
You're better than them,
but you're not better than me.

581
01:09:01,704 --> 01:09:04,298
Can she have the moccasins now?

582
01:09:10,846 --> 01:09:12,336
Yeah.

583
01:09:16,752 --> 01:09:18,379
Can l just--?

584
01:09:22,158 --> 01:09:24,422
l'm glad you were here.

585
01:09:33,102 --> 01:09:34,865
l was bitten by a rattlesnake.

586
01:09:37,339 --> 01:09:38,499
What?

587
01:09:38,941 --> 01:09:42,138
A good shaman gave me
two amulets.

588
01:09:44,680 --> 01:09:47,706
Told me not to eat
rabbit meat for a year...

589
01:09:48,484 --> 01:09:51,044
...to say my prayers every morning...

590
01:09:51,987 --> 01:09:54,888
...take care of my family,
and l might get well.

591
01:09:58,894 --> 01:10:01,385
You're telling me the only
reason you came back...

592
01:10:01,564 --> 01:10:04,431
...was because you were
following the say-so of some...

593
01:10:04,600 --> 01:10:06,568
...medicine man. ls that right?

594
01:10:06,869 --> 01:10:11,306
Yes. Absolutely. A rattlesnake
can make your soul...

595
01:10:14,443 --> 01:10:16,308
...very sick.

596
01:10:18,714 --> 01:10:21,274
That's likely not what
you want to hear.

597
01:10:21,450 --> 01:10:23,714
But it is the truth.

598
01:10:56,085 --> 01:11:03,321
We have eight girls. Now, we can go.

